result.execSummary:
The defendant Jessi M. Marshall was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony [Modifiers: Repeater, PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).
  • Violate State/County Institution Laws [Modifiers: Repeater, PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class C misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.73.
  • Resisting or Obstructing an Officer [Modifiers: Repeater], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 11:28 AM/Rm. 301/Prosecuting attorney Kelly L Hays in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Jessi M. Marshall in court.  Attorney John Zich in court for Jessi M. Marshall.  Court Reporter by Zoom.  Plea agreement.  On plea to Ct. 1, Ct. 2 and Ct. 7,  recommend:  Ct. 1 - sentence withheld, 4 years probation concurrent to any other supervision, costs, comply with supervision conditions in 21-CF-346.  Ct. 2 - 39 days jail, consecutive to any other sentence, costs, Ct. 7 - 1 year jail imposed and stayed, consecutive to any other sentence, probation, costs, same conditions.  Preliminary hearing was waived previously.  Plea questionnaire/waiver of rights form filed and reviewed with Def.  Ct. 1 - felony bail jumping, repeater, party to - no contest plea.  Ct. 2 - violate St./Co. Inst. Laws - no contest plea.  Ct. 7 - resisting - no contest plea.  Counts dismissed and read in:  Cts. 3, 4, 5, 6 and 8 for sentencing purposes on State's motion.  Def. advised of constitutional rights and right to jury trial.  Def. waives rights and jury trial.  Court advised Def. of elements and penalties.  Def. advised of possible deportation if not US citizen.  Court finds pleas entered freely and voluntarily.  Factual basis.  Court accepts pleas and finds Def. guilty of Cts. 1, 2 and 7.  Sentencing remarks by State.  Sentencing remarks by Def.'s Atty.  Def. makes statement to Court.  Court orders Ct. 1 - sentence withheld, 4 years probation, costs, DNA sample if not done and surcharge, comply with same conditions as in 21-CF-346.  Ct. 2 - 39 days jail, consecutive to any other sentence, huber, costs, DNA surcharge.  Ct. 7 - 1 year jail imposed and stayed, huber, consecutive to any other sentence, 2 years probation, costs, DNA surcharge, same conditions as in Ct. 1 and in 21-CF-346.  Credit - 39 days - time served on Ct. 2.  Def. advised of voting and firearm rights.  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.  $2,000 cash bond applied, balance to be returned to poster.  Def. advised of postconviction rights.  Recess 11:51 a.m.
Plea/sentencing hearing on July 28, 2022 at 11:15 am.

No illegal use or possession of controlled substances.  No contact with Kyle Roberts.
Amended

Deputy Travis Krueger, duly sworn on oath, testifies.  State asks Court take judicial notice of Langlade Co. Case #21-CF-34.  Court takes judicial notice.  State rests.  Def.'s Atty. calls Det. Sgt. Court reads case law.  State makes further argument.  Response by Def.'s Atty.  Court binds case over.  Arraignment scheduled.  Def.'s Atty. asks bond be addressed today.  10:02 a.m./Off the record to contact DA Gebert.  10:10 a.m./Back on record.  DA Gebert now appears by Zoom for the State.  Court has reviewed Def.'s motion regarding bond.  Argument by Def.'s Atty.  Response by State.  Response by Def.'s Atty.  Information filed with same charges as complaint.  Def.'s Atty. waives reading and pleads not guilty to all charges in information.  Court receives not guilty pleas and directs clerk to enter into the record.  Status conference scheduled for February 28, 2022 at 11:00 am.

records.addlTxt: 01:24 PM in Room 203. Defendant Jessi M. Marshall in court, in custody at the Langlade County Jail.  Elizabeth Gebert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Jessi M. Marshall appeared by video means. All appearances are by Zoom. Def. does not have copy of complaint; Court advises she will be provided with copy.  Def. advised of charges and penalties.  Def. on probation hold. State heard on bond, recommends $5,000 cash bond with conditions she have no contact with Kyle Roberts. Def. heard on bond.  Def. given atty rights and given 3 options, PD, hire own or court appointed atty. Remarks by the Court. The Court orders $4, 000 cash bond with conditions. Bond issue may be reviewed at a later date.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for January 31, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
